oc:kn_0d7a886e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When filling out competitor and own-product data templates" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Be honest and fair in competitor assessments — document real strengths, real weaknesses, and include 'not ideal for' and 'common complaints' sections." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Honest comparisons build trust with readers and avoid misleading claims that can backfire; also helps your own product positioning." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_1987fa15 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before page generation begins" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before generating comparison pages, ensure you have completed a full competitor data template (YAML) for both the competitor and your own product, covering pricing, features (rated 1-5), strengths, weaknesses, best_for, not_ideal_for, and migration notes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incomplete data leads to thin or inaccurate comparison pages that underperform in search and fail to convert." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_24afd15d a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any competitor comparison page" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Maintain a single source of truth for all competitor data in individual markdown files within a competitor_data/ directory. Each page pulls from this centralized data rather than duplicating information." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Centralized data ensures updating pricing or features once propagates everywhere, preventing inconsistencies across dozens of pages." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7ea9183f a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing footer navigation for competitor pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include up to 8 links per footer column for top competitors sorted by search volume, with a 'View all' link to the full index page." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Footer links provide sitewide internal linking equity; limiting to top 8 keeps the footer clean while maximizing SEO impact for highest-volume terms." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_7f631eac a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating or updating comparison pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never hardcode competitor data (pricing, features, strengths/weaknesses) directly into individual comparison pages. Always pull from the centralized competitor data files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hardcoded data leads to stale information across pages and makes maintenance unscalable as the number of competitors grows." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b51a3a37 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scaling competitor content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When adding a new comparison page, simultaneously: update the centralized data file, add the page to the relevant index, and update footer navigation for high-priority competitors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ensures all entry points (index pages, footer links, internal cross-links) remain current and pass link equity to new content." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

_:ref_004ebdb3cbd29647 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
